<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-1-5-pop-billion-million">
    <statement>
        <p>
            In 2011, the population of the United States was approximately 0.313 billion.
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use the fact that 1 billion = 1,000 million to write down two unit conversion fractions:
                    <me>
                        1 = \dfrac{<fillin fill="1.000" /> \text{ billion}}
                                        {<fillin fill="1000" /> \text{ million}}
                        \quad \text{and} \quad
                        1 = \dfrac{<fillin fill="1000" /> \text{ million}}
                                        {<fillin fill="1.000" /> \text{ billion}}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Writing the population as 0.313 billion seems strange. A more natural unit would be millions. Use the correct unit conversion fraction from above to rewrite the population in millions of people.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>